---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 0
eleventyNavigation: Home
title: Swiss Sovereign AI — Fine-Tuned Apertus, Run in Your Jurisdiction
description: sysf.io fine-tunes Apertus — Switzerland's open LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS — on your documents and runs it inside your infrastructure. Open weights your auditors can inspect, no US API in the loop, and you own the model.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, cta, icon, iconChip %}
{% from "partials/charts.njk" import statBand, hbarChart %}

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="circuit pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10 opacity-70 dark:opacity-20"></div>
  <div class="container-x grid items-center gap-12 py-20 md:grid-cols-12 md:py-28">
    <div class="md:col-span-7">
      <p class="eyebrow">Swiss Sovereign AI</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.05] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-6xl dark:text-white">
        AI for the data<br />you can't send away.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
        We fine-tune <strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Apertus</strong> — Switzerland's open LLM — on your documents and run it inside your infrastructure. You own the weights; no US API in the loop.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Book a call</a>
        <a href="/configure/" class="btn-secondary">Configure your build</a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm">
        {% for b in ["Swiss FADP / GDPR", "In-jurisdiction", "No data egress", "Open weights"] %}
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-medium text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">
          <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 bg-swiss"></span>{{ b }}
        </span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="md:col-span-5">
      {% include "partials/diagram.njk" %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Proof stats -->
<section class="container-x py-14 md:py-20">
  {% set stats = [
    {v:"94%", label:"Production accuracy", sub:"Canton of Ticino's fine-tuned Apertus-8B, in service on cantonal infrastructure"},
    {v:"22.4 → 45.4%", label:"Fine-tuning + retrieval", sub:"Correct answer plus exact citation on the public FINMA benchmark, when fine-tuning is added to retrieval"},
    {v:"100%", label:"Format compliance", sub:"From ~2% to fully machine-parseable output after fine-tuning"},
    {v:"0", label:"Bytes of data egress", sub:"No third-party LLM API in training or inference — zero egress is architectural"}
  ] %}
  {{ statBand(stats) }}
</section>

<!-- Measured proof -->
<section class="border-t border-ink-900/10 py-20 dark:border-white/10 md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12 md:items-center">
    <div class="md:col-span-5">
      {{ sectionHead("Measured, not promised", "We prove the numbers before you commit.", "A reproducible four-way ablation of Apertus-8B on Swiss FINMA circular Q&amp;A, scored deterministically. Only fine-tuning <em>and</em> retrieval together clear the production bar.") }}
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/reports/finma-ablation/" class="btn-ghost">Read the report</a>
        <a href="/resources/" class="btn-ghost">All resources</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="md:col-span-7">
      {% set legend = [
        {name:"Answer correct", cls:"bg-teal-300"},
        {name:"Answer + citation (production bar)", cls:"bg-teal-600"},
        {name:"Clears the bar", cls:"bg-red-600"}
      ] %}
      {% set groups = [
        {label:"A · Base model", bars:[{v:37.2, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:0.0, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"B · + Retrieval", bars:[{v:63.4, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:22.4, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"C · Fine-tuned", bars:[{v:44.8, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:1.6, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"D · Fine-tuned + retrieval", note:"the full system", bars:[{v:80.9, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:45.4, cls:"bg-red-600"}]}
      ] %}
      {{ hbarChart(groups, legend, "183 human-verified questions across 10 FINMA circulars (DE + EN). The production bar goes 22.4% → 45.4% only when fine-tuning and retrieval are combined.") }}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why sysf.io -->
<section class="border-t border-ink-900/10 bg-ink-900/[0.02] py-20 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/[0.02] md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
    {{ sectionHead("Why sysf.io", "A model you own, running where your data lives.") }}
    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
      {% set why = [
        {ic:"shield-check", t:"Sovereign & private", d:"Training and inference run inside your infrastructure — Swiss or EU jurisdiction, or fully air-gapped. Zero data egress, no US API."},
        {ic:"clipboard-check", t:"Measured before you commit", d:"Every engagement starts with an evaluation built from your own documents. You see the numbers before production is built."},
        {ic:"key", t:"Yours to keep", d:"Open weights, fine-tuned on your data. The model, the runbooks and a documented exit plan are deliverables — no lock-in."}
      ] %}
      {% for w in why %}
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
        {{ iconChip(w.ic) }}
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ w.t }}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ w.d }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="mt-8 text-base prose-muted">Built on <a class="link-underline" href="{{ site.baseModel.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apertus</a> — or a European or international open-weight base where your compliance allows. <a class="link-underline" href="/platform/">See how it ships end-to-end</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Industries -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("Industries", "Built for Switzerland's regulated sectors.") }}
  <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    {% set inds = [
      {ic:"landmark", t:"Banking & Finance", d:"Advisory copilots, KYC/AML processing, regulatory Q&A — on-prem, zero egress."},
      {ic:"heart-pulse", t:"Healthcare & Pharma", d:"Clinical documentation and research assistants — patient data stays in Switzerland."},
      {ic:"scale", t:"Legal & Compliance", d:"Multilingual contract analysis and legal research (DE/FR/IT), privilege-safe."},
      {ic:"building-2", t:"Government & Public", d:"Citizen services and DE/FR/IT translation on the administration's own infrastructure."},
      {ic:"shield-check", t:"Insurance", d:"Claims automation and policy Q&A copilots grounded in your documents."},
      {ic:"factory", t:"Manufacturing", d:"On-prem knowledge and maintenance assistants for the shop floor."}
    ] %}
    {% for i in inds %}
    <a href="/industries/" class="group rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-shadow hover:shadow-md dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
      {{ iconChip(i.ic) }}
      <h3 class="flex items-center justify-between text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">
        {{ i.t }}
        <span class="text-swiss opacity-0 transition-opacity group-hover:opacity-100">{{ icon("arrow-right", "h-4 w-4") }}</span>
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ i.d }}</p>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How it works -->
<section class="border-t border-ink-900/10 bg-ink-900/[0.02] py-20 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/[0.02] md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
  {{ sectionHead("The platform", "From your data to a system in production.") }}
  <ol class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-4">
    {% set steps = [
      {ic:"search", n:"1", t:"Scope & comply", d:"Use-case discovery and compliance scoping — FADP, GDPR, EU AI Act."},
      {ic:"sliders-horizontal", n:"2", t:"Fine-tune on Apertus", d:"Private, in-jurisdiction data prep and domain fine-tuning."},
      {ic:"workflow", n:"3", t:"Orchestrate", d:"Agents, RAG and tools wired to your systems, with guardrails."},
      {ic:"server", n:"4", t:"Deploy & operate", d:"Deployment in your tenancy, monitoring and iteration under support."}
    ] %}
    {% for s in steps %}
    <li class="relative border-t-2 border-swiss pt-5">
      <span class="mb-3 inline-flex text-teal-700 dark:text-teal-300">{{ icon(s.ic, "h-6 w-6") }}</span>
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-500">Step {{ s.n }}</div>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ s.t }}</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ s.d }}</p>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ol>
  <div class="mt-10"><a href="/platform/" class="btn-ghost">Explore the platform</a></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Resources teaser -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("Resources", "See the engineering — and run it yourself.", "The thinking behind the approach, the measured proof on public data, and a model you can run in your browser right now.") }}
  <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    {% set res = [
      {ic:"cpu", k:"Concept", t:"Small models, measured.", d:"Why a fine-tuned 4–8B beats a frontier API on your scoped task — with the honest limits.", u:"/concepts/small-models/"},
      {ic:"bar-chart-3", k:"Report", t:"Does fine-tuning actually help?", d:"A reproducible ablation on public FINMA data — fine-tuning plus retrieval doubles the bar.", u:"/reports/finma-ablation/"},
      {ic:"play", k:"Demo", t:"A model in your browser.", d:"A 1-bit, 1.7B model triages support messages on your own GPU — nothing leaves the tab.", u:"/demo/"}
    ] %}
    {% for r in res %}
    <a href="{{ r.u }}" class="group flex flex-col rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition hover:border-teal-600/40 hover:shadow-md dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-teal-700 dark:text-teal-300">{{ icon(r.ic, "h-3.5 w-3.5") }}{{ r.k }}</span>
      <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-bold tracking-tightest text-ink-900 group-hover:text-teal-700 dark:text-white dark:group-hover:text-teal-300">{{ r.t }}</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 flex-1 text-sm prose-muted">{{ r.d }}</p>
      <span class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700 dark:text-teal-300">Read{{ icon("arrow-right", "h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5") }}</span>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <div class="mt-10"><a href="/resources/" class="btn-ghost">Browse all resources</a></div>
</section>

{{ cta("Ready to own your AI?", "Book a scoping call. We'll pick one use case, agree the metrics, and scope a fixed-scope pilot that proves the numbers on your own documents.") }}
